						<div class="postbody">OK, I figured if I wanted to "allow" the left 8 tiles to be glitched, I'd have to have my second $2006 write fall "during the first tile" and write the adress of the SECOND tile. But then the PPU scrolls from the second tile at the next scanline so I had to add a $2005 write in the cases where the palette wasn't rewritten to have normal scroll.
<br />
<br />Yet I still can't get rid of the glitches. I've had setups without glitches on Nestopia, but with glitches on HW, and this for both NTSC and PAL.
<br />
<br />I uploaded everything on : <a href="http://jonathan.microclub.ch/window" class="postlink">http://jonathan.microclub.ch/window</a>
<br />Blargg, I uploaded the .chr file btw.</div>

					
